We are a growing Real Estate development firm in Downtown Newark, NJ seeking a talented energetic, creative, self-starter with 7-10 years of industry experience with solid organizational, listening, communication skills. You should have the ability to multitask and self-prioritize. You should enjoy collaboration and be a great team player.

Responsibilities:

Work with clients and design architects to conceptualize design. Direct team members to prepare digital presentations, FFE specifications and contract documents throughout concept design, schematic design and design development to construction phases.

Qualifications:

Bachelor of Architecture, Interior Design or Interior Architecture from an NAAB or CIDQ accredited school;
NYS Architectural Registration or NCIDQ preferred, but not required;
Proficient in Autocad;
Fluent in Sketch Up, Adobe Creative Suite, Microsoft Office;
Knowledgeable in 3D Modeling programs 3D Max/V-Ray a plu;
Knowledgeable in Revit, Bluebeam;
Experience with Construction Documents and FFE specifications;
Familiar with NYC/NJ interior building codes, ADA and building practices as applied to interior architecture;
Excellent English language communication skills;
Legally eligible to work in the United States without the need for sponsorship;
Salary commensurate with experience.
Email resume and portfolio in the link provided.

Do not call

